<p><strong>Reading left to right, the steps climb 1, 2, 3, 4, 5, 6, 7 blocks high — one taller each pass, because <code>y = y + 1</code> runs every loop.</strong></p>
<p><strong>Modify challenge.</strong> Change <strong>one</strong> thing and <strong>predict the new pattern before you run it</strong> — for example change <code>range(7)</code> to <code>range(10)</code>, or make the step <code>y = y + 2</code> (steeper). Write what will move, then build it and check.</p>
